Simulating CO T->P leakage from bandpass mismatch¶

In my previous posting I've shown how the bandpass mismatches due to CO 1-0 line leak into Q , U polarization maps.

We model the mismatch for both detector bandpass around the CO line ( see figure above) as

$$ d^A_t = f s_{CO} $$ $$ d^B_t = \epsilon f s_{CO} $$

where $f$ and $\epsilon $ parametrize the bandpass mismatch of the detector pair and $s_{CO} $ is the scanned CO intensity only map (see above, no polarization). So far we consider $f$ and $\epsilon $ constant during the whole observation period: ($f= 0.5 $ and $\epsilon = 0.3 $ )

We injected bandpass mismatches by simulating 1 yr of LB signal -only observations performed by 2 detector pair.

We therefore want to assess the level of T-> P leakage from CO lines to QU maps.

Sims w/ CO 1-0¶

In case of signal only sims, Madam destriper doesn't converge since the band mismatches don't behave as a common baseline to be fitted in the timestream; therefore I just considered binned coadded maps.

mco10b= hp.read_map('../CO_bandpass/madam_bmap_003.fits', field=range(3), verbose=False)

fig=pl.figure(figsize=(15,8))
mco10b[0]/=0.5
hp.mollview(mco10b[0] , cmap=cmap , sub=131, fig=fig,norm='hist',max=.01,min=0., title= ' CO1-0, T '  , unit= r'$K_{CMB}$ ')
hp.mollview(mco10b[1] , cmap=cmap , sub=132, fig=fig , title= '  Q ' , unit=  r'$K_{CMB}$ ', min=-1e-7, max=1e-7)
hp.mollview(mco10b[2], cmap=cmap , sub=133, fig=fig ,  title= ' U ' , unit=  r'$K_{CMB}$ ', min=-1e-7, max=1e-7)

Caption:Binned Maps obtained with the simulation setup as described above. Notice that a leakage of $1 \mu $K is observed both on Q and U maps.

We apply to the output maps a CO mask, excluding all the CO emission larger than $10 \mu $K, (obtained with a 5 deg smoothing of the Commander CO 10 map). Apodization length 1 deg, ($f_{sky}= 0.80$)

Finally, we estimate the BB power spectra by means of the pure estimator ( Grain et al 2009, Smith et al. 2006), by applying a Galactic mask to the maps. We also corrected by :

$$ f^2 (1- \epsilon)^2 \hat{C}_b $$ being $\hat{C}_b$ the estimated binned pure B power spectrum.
